The staff are very professional and have always made appropriate suggestions when I was undecided regarding the venue. There is no pressure to buy and they work tirelessly to make sure that your order is correct. Please find alternatives like paper bags, biodegradable utensils/packaging, and zero plastic options (there are many affordable choices available in market). I would gladly pay more if it’s slightly more expensive to be fully green, but being vegan isn’t only about health and diet, it’s being fully conscious of the environmental impact and our carbon footprint on this planet.

Small vegan counter serve shop in Harlem. They have a variety of vegan dishes, including wraps, burritos, mac n cheese,  burgers, as well as about 10-12 vegan dish imitations of meat items (fish/wings/etc). Price for the food by pound is 7.99$, which will give you more than enough. They also have brown rice and quinoa for a base for the bowl you can make yourself. I had a bowl with a little bit of 5 dishes, all of which were extremely delicious. The BEST thing they had however was the vegan chilli - which they incidentally  have a special for (4.99 for brown rice and chilli). I wish I had just gotten that because it was by far their best dish. The other fake meat items were still good, but not as good as that. Only disappointing thing was the mac n cheese - not worth trying since they have better stuff, and to be honest, vegan cheese anywhere is always disappointing.

This place is AMAZING!!! We've been in NYC for 2 weeks and have seen one or two vegan restaurants a day. This was BY FAR the best one yet. Great food, great prices and very nice and helpful staff. If you visit Harlem you HAVE to visit Uptown Veg. The vegan chicken drumsticks are the best chicken I've ever eaten. The vegan Mac&cheese was the first vegan Mac&cheese I actually liked in NYC. The curry is great and the chilli is great. They make their own juices, which also taste spot on. I highly recommend this place.

We brought our own containers to conserve the environment, reduce waste and cost to the restaurant, she weighed the container prior to ordering, then refused to take tare weiggt off the cost of our meal afterwards simply because she didn't know how. When I talked her through how to do it, by simply subtracting the original weight of the container off the total weight she refused and overcharged me and was super rude to me. Even the other customers behind me in the line tried telling her to take off the original weight and asked me if she overcharged me - which she did.  When we ordered our second order she couldn't count the change out and took her 6 times to count out of change to finally give us the correct amount at the end. Monique really set the tone for a horrible experience here, the rest of the staff were actually quite pleasant.

The food, generally enjoyed by all the attendees-- vegetarian & non- vegetarian, often attracts new clients, including non- vegetarians to the Restaurant from these events.
